cs.AI, cs.SY, cs.LG, cs.RO, cs.DS 

The paper describes a planning approach to solve a practical problem of efficient use of multiple batteries, which involves modelling and solving a Markov Decision Problem. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the sub-categories of Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI), Systems and Control (cs.SY), and Robotics (cs.RO). The paper also mentions the use of Monte Carlo sampling for policy learning, which is a common technique in Machine Learning (cs.LG) and the discretisation of the temporal dimension, which is a technique used in Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS). Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.AI, cs.SY, cs.LG, cs.RO, and cs.DS, in that order.
